{
  "name": "Generate visual assets for completed spec task",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "[Implements: R32.3 / R32.5] After every spec task completion, scan the spec's design.md and tasks.md for visual asset references and generate any missing assets via the kiro-gpt-bridge MCP tools.",
  "enabled": true,
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[R32.3 — visual-asset hook for spec authoring] Predicate (exit silently if any check fails):\n  1. The just-completed task MUST belong to a spec under `.kiro/specs/**`. If the task is not from a spec, stop.\n  2. The owning spec's `design.md` OR `tasks.md` MUST contain at least one of the keywords (case-insensitive): `logo`, `hero`, `icon`, `image`, `mockup`, `illustration`, `background`. If neither file mentions any of these, stop.\n\nOtherwise, scan the spec docs for the just-completed task: read `design.md` and `tasks.md` and identify every visual asset referenced (logos, hero images, icon sets, UI mockups, illustrations, backgrounds). For each referenced asset whose target path is not yet on disk, call the appropriate kiro-gpt-bridge MCP tool from the kiro-gpt-bridge MCP server to produce it:\n  - `kiroGpt.generateLogo` / `generate_logo` for logos\n  - `kiroGpt.generateHero` / `generate_hero` for hero images\n  - `kiroGpt.generateIconSet` / `generate_icon_set` for icon sets\n  - `kiroGpt.generateUiMockup` / `generate_ui_mockup` for UI mockups\n  - `kiroGpt.generateImage` / `generate_image` for any other illustration or background\nDerive each tool's `prompt` and `assetCategory`/`kind` from the spec context (section heading, surrounding paragraph, task description). After each tool call, update the spec docs (and any source files generated by the task) to reference the `savedPath` returned by the tool. Do not emit placeholder paths."
  }
}
